Package lb provides a simple and efficient load balancer.

There are four different ways to select a resource depending on whether you
wish to use the resource priority or weight.

	┌───────────────────────┬─────────────────────┬───────────────────┐
	│                       │ Weighted resources  │    Any weight     │
	├───────────────────────┼─────────────────────┼───────────────────┤
	│ Prioritized resources │ PriorityWeighted(n) │ PriorityRandom(n) │
	├───────────────────────┼─────────────────────┼───────────────────┤
	│ Any priority          │ RandomWeighted()    │ Random()          │
	└───────────────────────┴─────────────────────┴───────────────────┘

$ go test -bench . -benchmem
	goos: linux
	goarch: amd64
	pkg: github.com/esote/lb
	BenchmarkPriorityRandom-6     	100000000	        14.1 ns/op	       0 B/op	       0 allocs/op
	BenchmarkPriorityWeighted-6   	50000000	        39.4 ns/op	       0 B/op	       0 allocs/op
	BenchmarkRandom-6             	30000000	        45.4 ns/op	       0 B/op	       0 allocs/op
	BenchmarkRandomWeighted-6     	30000000	        57.8 ns/op	       0 B/op	       0 allocs/op
	BenchmarkCryptoRand-6         	 2000000	       991 ns/op	       8 B/op	       1 allocs/op
	PASS
	ok  	github.com/esote/lb	10.547s
